									REAL TIME SYSTEMS
							      		RUSHANG V KARIA
							
								
SCHEDULING ANALYSIS OF EDF, RM , DM AND FIXED PRIORITY ALGORITHMS FOR REAL TIME SYSTEMS								

User input is Enabled. WCET =max Execution time
This program was developed on a computer with a resolution of 1360x768.
Please make sure that you view the code in only this or a greater resolution for convenient viewing.
Also please make sure that you are viewing it in fullscreen

For best viewing open in gedit  (fullscreen)
Go to edit select preferences.
Enable line numbers

Go to font and colors
Select Oblivion

-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x-x*/
-----------------------------------------
INSTRUCTIONS TO COMPILE
-----------------------------------------
Please browse to source and type "make" at the console.

Please make sure that the linker knows where to find the math library else please make sure you give the correct path to gcc command

-----------------------------------------
INSTRUCTIONS TO RUN
-----------------------------------------
Type "./Program" at the console

The report is shown after you enter all the tasksets

##################################################################################################################
NOTE: you may have to be the root user if the current folder does not allow normal users to read/write to files.
      This program writes 6 files to the same directory from where it is run
##################################################################################################################

-----------------------------------------
BASIC ERRORS THAT MIGHT BE ENCOUNTERED
-----------------------------------------
If the program crashes please reduce the limit of MAX_* in the header file since it might be the case that the system does not have enough memory.

Also try raising MAX_MEMORY to more than 1000 if the no of tasks is high in number. Since this variable keeps track of the RT,Loading Factor tests,
having its value greater than the no of iterations required for convergence is crucial.


